system.description:
Persuasive: You gain +1 Influence

You can always…

  • Tell a little white lie

  • Say something you're not supposed to.

  • Change the subject abruptly.

  • Ask: "Are you sure about that?"
canAlways: Say something you're not supposed to.

system.description:
Seafarer: You gain +1 Nature

You can always…

  • Tell which way is north.

  • Tend to a ship.

  • Say: "I have just the story for this."

  • Ask: "What's your story?"
canAlways: Say: "I have just the story for this."

system.description:
Civil: You gain +1 Influence

You can always…

  • Make it about you

  • Find audience with local nobility

  • Say: "I'm above this."

  • Ask: "Who's in charge here?"

Criminal: You gain +1 Scoundrel

You can always…

  • Find a way out from between a rock and a hard place

  • Spill the beans

  • Find a way in somewhere you shouldn't be

  • Have something you're not supposed to.
canAlways: Find a way out from between a rock and a hard place.
Find a way in somewhere you shouldn't be.
Have something you're not supposed to.

system.description:
Civil: You gain +1 Influence

You can always…

  • Stand up for your allies

  • Keep both eyes on someone

  • Stomp your foot and get everyone's attention.

  • Ask: "What aren't you telling me?"
canAlways: Stomp your foot and get everyone's attention.

system.description:
Knowledgeable: You gain +1 Lore

You can always…

  • Cite your sources, hoping they help your case.

  • Locate something in a library, if it’s there.

  • Jot something important down.

  • Ask: “Could you explain?”
canAlways: Cite your sources, hoping they help your case.
Locate something in a library, if it’s there.

system.description:
Civil: You gain +1 Influence

You can always…

  • Find something worth buying.

  • Appraise a ware.

  • Offer someone a deal

  • Ask: "How can I help?"

Musician: You gain +1 Influence

You can always...

  • Play a tune.

  • Make an audience from a crowd.

  • Say: “You remind me of someone.”

  • Ask: “Can I stay here?”
canAlways: Make an audience from a crowd.

system.description:
Knowledgeable: You gain +1 Lore

You can always…

  • Make a small and harmless contraption.

  • Have the right tool for the job.

  • Marvel at someone's creation.

  • Ask: "Can I get a hand?"
canAlways: Make a small and harmless contraption.
Have the right tool for the job.

system.description:
Religious: You gain +1 Religion

You can always…

  • Offer a small prayer.

  • Place your faith in those around you.

  • Give someone the benefit of the doubt.

  • Tell someone about your faith.
canAlways: Place your faith in those around you.
Give someone the benefit of the doubt.

system.description:
Naturalist: You gain +1 Nature

You can always…

  • Find enough food for you and your party in the wilderness

  • Protect yourself from harsh weather

  • Continue onward

  • Ask: "Do you need a hand?"
canAlways: Find enough food for you and your party in the wilderness.

system.description:
Naturalist: You gain +1 Nature

You can always…

  • Stare off into the distance

  • Say the quiet part out loud

  • Do something out of the ordinary

  • Ask: "Can you explain?"
canAlways: Say the quiet part out loud.
Do something out of the ordinary.

system.description:
Knowledgeable: You gain +1 Lore

You can always…

  • Tend to someone's wounds

  • Scribble something down illegibly

  • Say: "Everything's gonna be ok."

  • Ask: "Can you explain what's wrong?"
